(SOLDIERS YELLING)

17:27.936 --> 17:31.687
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

17:32.677 --> 17:36.172
(JET ENGINE ROARING)

17:36.174 --> 17:37.962
(BOMBS EXPLODING)

17:37.964 --> 17:39.011
(GUNS FIRING)

17:39.013 --> 17:41.561
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

17:41.563 --> 17:43.461
(HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING)

17:43.463 --> 17:45.880
(GUN FIRING)

17:50.562 --> 17:52.622
(SOLDIERS YELLING)

17:52.624 --> 17:55.707
(JET ENGINE ROARING)

17:57.813 --> 17:58.644
(GUN FIRING)

17:58.646 --> 17:59.630
MAN: You're a hard man to catch.

17:59.632 --> 18:02.382
(DOORBELL RINGS)

18:05.421 --> 18:08.439
(DOORBELL RINGS)

18:08.441 --> 18:11.124
(DRAMATIC TONAL MUSIC)

18:11.126 --> 18:13.876
(DOORBELL RINGS)

18:23.862 --> 18:27.029
(GROOVING JAZZ MUSIC)

18:53.439 --> 18:55.939
(CAT MEOWING)

19:02.224 --> 19:04.724
(CAT MEOWING)

20:23.464 --> 20:26.547
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

20:28.561 --> 20:30.056
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

20:30.058 --> 20:31.523
Hey, how's my daughter?

20:31.525 --> 20:33.698
TRICIA: Oh, fine, fine, really great.

20:34.545 --> 20:37.503
Look, Dad, I'm about to dash out the door,

20:37.505 --> 20:39.813
but I was wondering if you
still have that picture of Mom

20:39.815 --> 20:41.263
that I adore so much?

20:41.265 --> 20:42.800
Which one's that honey?

20:42.802 --> 20:44.113
TRICIA: The one of her at the beach.

20:44.115 --> 20:46.220
You know, in the sun hat.

20:46.222 --> 20:47.333
I've got it.

20:47.335 --> 20:49.843
TRICIA: Oh great, be a
dear and send me a copy,

20:49.845 --> 20:51.003
would you Dad?

20:51.005 --> 20:51.836
Sure.

20:51.838 --> 20:53.443
TRICIA: Oh, that's great.

20:53.445 --> 20:54.578
Thanks a bunch.

20:55.445 --> 20:56.953
Sorry I can't chat now,

20:56.955 --> 20:58.723
but I'll try and call you tomorrow.

20:58.725 --> 20:59.556
Okay, Dad?

20:59.558 --> 21:01.333
Okay, honey.

21:01.335 --> 21:02.766
TRICIA: Call you later, love you.

21:02.768 --> 21:04.983
Love you, too, bye-bye.

21:04.985 --> 21:08.152
(OMINOUS TONAL MUSIC)

21:17.119 --> 21:19.786
(DOOR KNOCKING)

21:25.565 --> 21:26.398
Morning, sir.

21:28.555 --> 21:31.123
Well, yes, I'm conducting a
survey for the Census Bureau.

21:31.125 --> 21:32.343
May I ask you a few questions?

21:32.345 --> 21:33.946
How long will this take?

21:33.948 --> 21:36.503
Just a couple of minutes, sir.

21:36.505 --> 21:38.553
I did one of these things
a couple of years ago.

21:38.555 --> 21:40.223
Thought it was every 10 years.

21:40.225 --> 21:43.523
Oh, well, yes sir, well this
is an ad hoc regional survey.

21:43.525 --> 21:44.933
What do you wanna know?

21:44.935 --> 21:47.723
May I ask which party you identify with?

21:47.725 --> 21:49.575
One with the most booze and broads.

21:50.455 --> 21:52.563
Oh, (LAUGHS) very funny sir.

21:52.565 --> 21:54.515
I'm glad it meets with your approval.

21:55.665 --> 21:57.263
Independent.

21:57.265 --> 21:58.853
Independent, yes sir.

21:58.855 --> 22:00.563
Now how many in your household?

22:00.565 --> 22:02.988
Just one, unless you count my cat.

22:02.990 --> 22:05.133
(LAUGHS) I hear it now.

22:05.135 --> 22:07.243
And what is your ethnicity, sir?

22:07.245 --> 22:09.443
What the hell difference does that make?

22:09.445 --> 22:11.033
We just have to ask, sir.

22:11.035 --> 22:13.563
And you can't tell by looking at me?

22:13.565 --> 22:15.383
We need to hear it from the occupant.

22:15.385 --> 22:17.213
Okay, what if I said I'm black?

22:17.215 --> 22:18.153
Are you, sir?

22:18.155 --> 22:19.123
No.

22:19.125 --> 22:22.098
I'm a mixture of Hottentot,
Macedonian, and Faeroese.

22:24.615 --> 22:26.033
Uh.

22:26.035 --> 22:27.503
Caucasian.

22:27.505 --> 22:29.303
Caucasian, yes sir.

22:29.305 --> 22:30.883
How many more of these
questions do you have?

22:30.885 --> 22:31.893
Well there's a few more...

22:31.895 --> 22:34.233
Yep, okay, well I don't have
time for it pal, that's it,

22:34.235 --> 22:36.115
my phone, too, I gotta go (MUMBLES).

22:36.117 --> 22:37.383
Oh, well, it'll just
take a few more minutes.

22:37.385 --> 22:38.218
Sorry.

22:39.658 --> 22:40.489
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

22:40.491 --> 22:42.953
(DOOR KNOCKING)

22:42.955 --> 22:44.033
Look, I said I didn't have...

22:44.035 --> 22:45.163
Sir, we really need to...

22:45.165 --> 22:46.373
We don't need to do anything!

22:46.375 --> 22:48.090
I'm through, okay, no more.

22:48.092 --> 22:49.493
You know the Bureau won't give up.

22:49.495 --> 22:50.963
They'll just keep sending more people.

22:50.965 --> 22:51.798
Let 'em send!

23:02.257 --> 23:05.007
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

23:17.228 --> 23:20.311
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

23:25.155 --> 23:25.986
Yeah.

23:25.988 --> 23:27.133
TRICIA: Hi, Dad.

23:27.135 --> 23:29.899
Oh, sorry, honey, I got
robocalls on the brain.

23:29.901 --> 23:30.732
TRICIA: Getting them a lot?

23:30.734 --> 23:31.773
All the time.

23:31.775 --> 23:33.193
TRICIA: Well, we get
them sometimes, too.

23:33.195 --> 23:35.673
Anyway, I just thought I'd check
in to see how you're doing?

23:35.675 --> 23:37.895
G.T.: Yeah, just sailing along.

23:37.897 --> 23:39.523
TRICIA: (laughs) Is
that pussy cat I hear?

23:39.525 --> 23:41.733
She's fine, 'course she's senile,

23:41.735 --> 23:43.396
you know, since that surgery.

23:43.398 --> 23:44.393
(CAT MEOWING)

23:44.395 --> 23:46.683
Too damn much anesthesia.

23:46.685 --> 23:48.489
TRICIA: You told me.

23:48.491 --> 23:49.891
Did I?

23:49.893 --> 23:50.913
That's right, I did, didn't I?

23:50.915 --> 23:52.733
TRICIA: Poor thing, don't you think

23:52.735 --> 23:54.003
she should be put to sleep?

23:54.005 --> 23:54.907
Oh, honey, don't say that,

23:54.909 --> 23:56.866
you know, that's my little buddy.

23:56.868 --> 23:57.743
(CAT MEOWING)

23:57.745 --> 24:00.123
You know she's entitled to live her life.

24:00.125 --> 24:02.863
TRICIA: Why don't you get another dog?

24:02.865 --> 24:04.633
Because I would die before it,

24:04.635 --> 24:06.366
and it would just end up
in the pound, that's why.

24:06.368 --> 24:07.703
TRICIA: Come on, Dad.

24:07.705 --> 24:09.268
You have many years left.

24:09.270 --> 24:10.983
(LAUGHS) Your mouth to God's ears.

24:10.985 --> 24:12.513
TRICIA: Well, anyway, I sure wish

24:12.515 --> 24:14.233
we could dash over there for a visit.

24:14.235 --> 24:15.813
Phoenix is not that far you know?

24:15.815 --> 24:18.930
TRICIA: I know, but things
are just so hectic over here.

24:18.932 --> 24:20.553
You know Patty's planning her wedding,

24:20.555 --> 24:24.413
I've got my job, plus library
functions draining my time,

24:24.415 --> 24:25.943
and don't even ask about Jeff.

24:25.945 --> 24:29.163
He's so busy since his promotion,
you wouldn't believe it.

24:29.165 --> 24:32.993
Well, you got your hands full
with a family, I know that.

24:32.995 --> 24:35.061
Just miss ya that's all.

24:35.063 --> 24:37.133
And I wish my damn doctor
would let me travel.

24:37.135 --> 24:39.453
TRICIA: We'll get together soon.

24:39.455 --> 24:41.293
Are you taking care of yourself?

24:41.295 --> 24:42.327
Oh yeah.

24:42.329 --> 24:44.323
TRICIA: You're not
drinking too much are you?

24:44.325 --> 24:46.743
Just a, not much, a glass now and then.

24:46.745 --> 24:49.338
TRICIA: Well, everything in moderation.

24:49.340 --> 24:50.171
That's what they say.

24:50.173 --> 24:53.203
TRICIA: Well, okay, Dad,
I've got to run, love you.

24:53.205 --> 24:55.593
Geez Louise, already?

24:55.595 --> 24:57.770
Okay, honey, love you, too.

24:57.772 --> 24:59.152
TRICIA: Take care.

24:59.154 --> 25:00.210
Bye-bye.

25:00.212 --> 25:03.462
(UPTEMPO BRIGHT MUSIC)

25:04.321 --> 25:06.971
Okay little buddy,
where are ya, chow time.

25:06.973 --> 25:10.231
You got lobster, you got
king crab, you got sushi.

25:10.233 --> 25:11.975
Where are ya?

25:11.977 --> 25:13.310
Beef wellington.

25:14.272 --> 25:15.522
Come on, buddy.

25:17.622 --> 25:19.420
Where are ya?

25:19.422 --> 25:20.760
I bet you're down here.

25:20.762 --> 25:22.059
(LAUGHS)

25:22.061 --> 25:25.061
There you are, come on you little...

25:26.723 --> 25:29.806
(SOMBER PIANO MUSIC)

25:48.280 --> 25:50.031
T.K. VOICEOVER: Well Trish,

25:50.033 --> 25:53.283
you needn't worry about my cat anymore.

25:54.483 --> 25:57.650
(OMINOUS TONAL MUSIC)

26:06.363 --> 26:07.753
WOMAN: You have called the office

26:07.755 --> 26:09.413
of the district attorney.

26:09.415 --> 26:12.526
For directions in English, press one.

26:12.528 --> 26:14.269
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

26:14.271 --> 26:17.781
Why do I have press one,
in my own damn country?

26:17.783 --> 26:20.443
(NUMBER BEEPING)
(PHONE DIAL RINGING)

26:20.445 --> 26:22.295
WOMAN: District attorney's office.

26:23.625 --> 26:27.943
Yeah, where do I go to file
a complaint about robocalls?

26:27.945 --> 26:29.563
WOMAN: What is it?

26:29.565 --> 26:33.433
Robocalls, you know,
sales calls, endless calls.

26:33.435 --> 26:35.603
WOMAN: Have you gone
on the don't call list?

26:35.605 --> 26:37.283
I'm on the don't call list.

26:37.285 --> 26:38.633
They don't give a damn.

26:38.635 --> 26:40.823
WOMAN: Will you hold please?

26:40.825 --> 26:42.381
Yes, I'll hold.

26:42.383 --> 26:45.966
(UPBEAT BRIGHT HOLD MUSIC)

26:52.405 --> 26:53.292
MAN: Hi, have you been helped?

26:53.294 --> 26:54.127
No I have not been helped.

26:55.155 --> 26:57.651
MAN: How may I direct your call, sir?

26:57.653 --> 27:00.713
(T.K. LAUGHS)

27:00.715 --> 27:01.548
Nevermind.

27:05.615 --> 27:08.128
Nobody gives a shit, that's
just a waste of time.

27:09.935 --> 27:11.604
What the hell.

27:11.606 --> 27:14.606
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

27:17.274 --> 27:19.583
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

27:19.585 --> 27:21.023
This is G.T.

27:21.025 --> 27:22.225
MAN: Hello, Mr. Benz.

27:23.528 --> 27:26.103
What is wrong with you people?

27:26.105 --> 27:28.593
Don't you know I'll never
by jack crap from you?

27:28.595 --> 27:30.833
MAN: Can I ask you what
is your monthly power bill?

27:30.835 --> 27:32.700
Can I have your social security number?

27:32.702 --> 27:35.339
How 'bout your wife's cell
phone number, I could use that.

27:35.341 --> 27:37.420
(DRAMATIC ORCHESTRAL MUSIC)

27:37.422 --> 27:38.253
MAN: You might save as much as...

27:38.255 --> 27:39.698
Just kiss my royal fanny.

27:58.056 --> 28:01.056
(CAR ALARM BEEPING)

28:15.179 --> 28:18.096
(SLOW PIANO MUSIC)

28:30.970 --> 28:33.637
(DOOR KNOCKING)

28:35.285 --> 28:37.457
- Hey Doc, how you doing?
- Hey, good, how are you?

28:37.459 --> 28:38.290
T.K.: Good to see ya.

28:38.292 --> 28:40.873
DR. FRANKLIN: Nice to see you.

28:40.875 --> 28:41.747
Well, what's the story?

28:41.749 --> 28:43.523
(DR. FRANKLIN SIGHS)

28:43.525 --> 28:44.358
Well,

28:45.565 --> 28:47.365
you're cholesterol levels are lousy.

28:48.525 --> 28:50.978
You're enzymes for your
liver are marginal.

28:51.925 --> 28:53.425
And your blood pressure is up.

28:54.694 --> 28:56.807
So I'm in pretty good shape?

28:56.809 --> 28:57.793
(DR. FRANKLIN CHUCKLES)

28:57.795 --> 28:59.493
For a corpse.

28:59.495 --> 29:01.018
How have you been feeling?

29:01.020 --> 29:03.133
Well I feel all right, but...

29:03.135 --> 29:04.173
Yeah?

29:04.175 --> 29:05.925
They're a couple of times when I,

29:07.185 --> 29:10.123
I wasn't sure where I
was for a few seconds.

29:10.125 --> 29:11.837
What were you going right before then?

29:11.839 --> 29:14.189
Before, I don't know,
nothing special really.

29:15.050 --> 29:16.963
Were you drinking at the time?

29:16.965 --> 29:18.265
I don't remember, maybe.

29:19.625 --> 29:21.873
How much you been drinking these days?

29:21.875 --> 29:23.443
Not that much.

29:23.445 --> 29:25.248
Remember, I'm your doctor.

29:26.425 --> 29:27.256
Well, I don't know, maybe I'm drinking

29:27.258 --> 29:30.103
a little bit too much,
but I never get drunk.

29:30.105 --> 29:32.593
You don't have to be
drunk to have a problem.

29:32.595 --> 29:34.223
Well,

29:34.225 --> 29:36.183
it's kinda odd, Doc, you know?

29:36.185 --> 29:37.403
What's that?

29:37.405 --> 29:38.668
I know I'm pretty sick,

29:39.565 --> 29:41.898
but I just don't feel it most the time.

29:42.735 --> 29:43.568
Well,

29:44.725 --> 29:46.387
you seem to be hanging in there.

29:46.389 --> 29:48.783
(CHUCKLES) Despite my best efforts.

29:48.785 --> 29:50.353
It's a paradox.

29:50.355 --> 29:51.408
Still no travel?

29:52.765 --> 29:54.503
You really shouldn't fly.

29:54.505 --> 29:57.333
What if I take the
train or drive to Phoenix?

29:57.335 --> 29:58.603
What happens if you're halfway there

29:58.605 --> 29:59.855
and there's an emergency?

30:01.045 --> 30:03.007
How should I put this?

30:03.009 --> 30:04.983
(SUSPENSEFUL TONAL MUSIC)

30:04.985 --> 30:06.835
Your condition is fragile, my friend.

30:09.305 --> 30:11.703
You've been hanging in there, but,

30:11.705 --> 30:12.655
I wouldn't push it.

30:14.241 --> 30:17.213
Is your daughter aware of your condition?

30:17.215 --> 30:18.773
You know, I don't wanna worry her,

30:18.775 --> 30:21.353
and she can't do anything about it anyway.

30:21.355 --> 30:22.505
Tell me something, Doc,

30:24.325 --> 30:27.063
how does a man know if
he's getting Alzheimer's?

30:27.065 --> 30:28.323
Why do you ask?

30:28.325 --> 30:31.325
Well, you know, my memory
just hasn't been quite the same.

30:32.625 --> 30:34.043
Well I don't see any indication,

30:34.045 --> 30:36.813
but alcohol surely doesn't help.

30:36.815 --> 30:38.533
Especially if you're on medication.

30:38.535 --> 30:39.885
Yeah, it's not that much.

30:40.895 --> 30:43.533
All right, well let me
know if it gets any worse.

30:43.535 --> 30:45.563
I'm gonna increase your BP medicine

30:45.565 --> 30:49.173
from 150 milligrams to 200 milligrams.

30:49.175 --> 30:50.118
You're the boss.

30:52.264 --> 30:54.347
(GROANS)

30:55.395 --> 30:56.545
Tell me something, Doc.

30:59.205 --> 31:00.828
How much time do I have?

31:02.865 --> 31:04.578
DR. FRANKLIN: Now I'm a fortune teller?

31:06.165 --> 31:08.565
With all things considered
as you like to say.

31:10.575 --> 31:11.408
Look.

31:14.032 --> 31:15.388
You might have a few years,

31:16.335 --> 31:17.435
could be a few months.

31:20.525 --> 31:21.408
Live your life.

31:22.885 --> 31:24.735
Enjoy yourself, don't worry about it.

31:26.263 --> 31:28.408
What I worry about is what's up here.

31:29.425 --> 31:31.233
My whole world's up there.

31:31.235 --> 31:32.068
My whole life.

31:33.105 --> 31:34.755
Forgetfulness is a part of age.

31:36.105 --> 31:38.150
Well that part I don't need.

31:38.152 --> 31:38.983
(DR. FRANKLIN CHUCKLES)

31:38.985 --> 31:40.829
I'll see ya next time.

31:40.831 --> 31:42.348
Okay, Doc, take it easy.

31:42.350 --> 31:45.600
(DRAMATIC TONAL MUSIC)

32:01.215 --> 32:04.965
(DRAMATIC PIANO TONAL MUSIC)

32:22.039 --> 32:25.122
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

32:27.309 --> 32:29.666
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

32:29.668 --> 32:30.927
MAN: Mr. Benz.

32:30.929 --> 32:33.713
(HEART POUNDING)

32:33.715 --> 32:36.882
(INTENSE TONAL MUSIC)

32:42.880 --> 32:46.380
(EERIE SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC)

32:49.770 --> 32:52.333
Yeah I'm trying to reach the
office of Congressman Garcia.

32:52.335 --> 32:54.785
WOMAN: This is his
office, how may I help you?

32:56.260 --> 32:57.393
Well, may I speak to him?

32:57.395 --> 32:59.592
WOMAN: May I ask what this is about?

32:59.594 --> 33:01.736
(SIGHS) I don't wanna repeat myself,

33:01.738 --> 33:02.653
can I just talk to him?

33:02.655 --> 33:04.173
WOMAN: The congressman is quite busy

33:04.175 --> 33:05.713
as I'm sure you can imagine.

33:05.715 --> 33:06.546
If you'll tell me...

33:06.548 --> 33:07.423
Well I'm busy, too.

33:07.425 --> 33:09.703
I won't talk more than
a couple of minutes.

33:09.705 --> 33:11.638
WOMAN: What is your name, sir?

33:11.640 --> 33:12.663
(G.T. SIGHS)

33:12.665 --> 33:14.593
G.T., G.T. Benz.

33:14.595 --> 33:16.025
WOMAN: G.T. Benz, I'll see if

33:16.027 --> 33:16.858
- he can take your call.
- Fine.

33:16.860 --> 33:17.785
(NUMBER BEEPING)
(PHONE DIAL RINGING)

33:17.787 --> 33:20.193
(PLAYFUL HOLD MUSIC)

33:20.195 --> 33:21.763
- Hello, sir?
- Yes.

33:21.765 --> 33:23.690
WOMAN: Sir, I'm sorry, but
he's in a conference just now.

33:23.692 --> 33:25.303
I just wanna talk to him about

33:25.305 --> 33:28.043
these bloody robocalls I'm getting.

33:28.045 --> 33:29.183
- Robocalls?
- Robocalls.

33:29.185 --> 33:30.493
WOMAN: Wouldn't that be something

33:30.495 --> 33:31.773
you'd talk to the phone company?

33:31.775 --> 33:34.488
I tried that, I need some muscle here.

33:35.385 --> 33:36.943
WOMAN: Sir, have you tried our website?

33:36.945 --> 33:37.835
There's a place where you can...

33:37.837 --> 33:38.960
Screw the website!

33:38.962 --> 33:42.782
(PHONE CLACKING)
(DIAL TONE BUZZING)

33:42.784 --> 33:44.951
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

33:44.953 --> 33:46.611
(SIGHS)

33:46.613 --> 33:47.530
Here we go.

33:51.573 --> 33:53.073
Ah, boy.

33:56.702 --> 33:59.452
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

34:13.491 --> 34:17.074
(MELODIC ORCHESTRAL MUSIC)

34:35.831 --> 34:37.338
Listen to this, honey.

34:39.375 --> 34:42.027
Gather ye rosebuds while ye may,

34:43.014 --> 34:45.078
Old Time is still a-flying;

34:46.705 --> 34:49.838
and this same flower that smiles today,

34:51.175 --> 34:53.318
tomorrow will be dying.

34:58.455 --> 35:01.822
Ol' Bob Herrick pretty well
nails it, doesn't he, honey?

35:08.625 --> 35:11.849
We're no more important
than gophers in the garden.

35:11.851 --> 35:15.101
(DRAMATIC TONAL MUSIC)

35:20.161 --> 35:23.244
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

35:25.303 --> 35:28.386
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

35:29.853 --> 35:34.353
("THE SIDEWALK TALKS" BY TRE HOUSTON)

